review_blob: Had really high expectations for this beer and was expecting a hoptastic IPA.  I was surprised to see very little head and a very thick carmely taste that finishes with a strong alcoholic flavor.  Good just different that what I was hoping for.
Golden color, sweet malty smell with a slight hop aroma too.  Great bitter pale ale with a good malt and hop flavor.
Nice dark color with a thick slightly brown head, there is a mild initial taste that ends with a nice hoppy bitter flavor.  Great winter time beer.
